nl_problem:
# Task: Nested Logic Test (Depth 10)
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: checkNested(self, x0: int, x1: int, x2: int, x3: int, x4: int, x5: int, x6: int, x7: int, x8: int, x9: int) -> bool

# Objective:
This is a test of structural nesting. Return True ONLY if all the following conditions are met:
1. x0 is greater than 0
2. x1 is greater than 0
3. x2 is greater than 0
4. x3 is greater than 0
5. x4 is greater than 0
6. x5 is greater than 0
7. x6 is greater than 0
8. x7 is greater than 0
9. x8 is greater than 0
10. x9 is greater than 0

Each condition must be checked inside the previous one (nested if statements).
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "checkNested")
  (signature ( (x0 int) (x1 int) (x2 int) (x3 int) (x4 int) (x5 int) (x6 int) (x7 int) (x8 int) (x9 int) ) bool)
  (constraints
    (constraint "All input integers must be greater than 0.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Return True only if all the following conditions are met:")
    (rule "x0 is greater than 0")
    (rule "x1 is greater than 0")
    (rule "x2 is greater than 0")
    (rule "x3 is greater than 0")
    (rule "x4 is greater than 0")
    (rule "x5 is greater than 0")
    (rule "x6 is greater than 0")
    (rule "x7 is greater than 0")
    (rule "x8 is greater than 0")
    (rule "x9 is greater than 0")
    (return "True if all conditions are met, False otherwise.")
  ))
